

National "Finland on the web" campaign was launched on Monday in Finland in a bid to increase citizens' knowledge of the Internet.

The campaign "Finland on the web" is part of the Finnish Government Information Society Programme and it is organized in close cooperation with companies, municipalities, regional councils and various state organizations.

During Nov. 7-11, libraries and citizens' service centers of over 280 municipalities in Finland will participate in this event and provide e-services training for free.

The event targets especially the working-age population and the elderly, local media reported.

